Key Match Events: Kagiso Rabada had Liam Livingstone caught at deep backward square off a full toss - and celebrated in his face - and only gave away four runs in his final over.
Marco Jansen sent down a phenomenal penultimate over, bowling into the pitch and taking pace off, and conceded only seven runs, leaving Anrich Nortje with 13 to defend off the last over.
Anrich Nortje successfully defended 13 runs in the final over in a tense finish.
Pre-Game Insights: England's planning against Quinton de Kock was spot on as they chose to open the bowling with Reece Topley and Moeen Ali, both of whom have had the better of de Kock in the past.
Post-Match Reflections: De Kock wins match-ups and gets a life
Quinton de Kock's fifty was the big difference between the teams
Miscellaneous Highlights: Phil Salt was tempted into an aerial drive off Rabada but did not hit it as well as he hoped and Hendricks leapt two-handed to his left to hold on to a spectacular catch.
Keshav Maharaj tossed the ball up, Bairstow cut and Nortje flung himself to his right at backward point to grab a stunner.
Klaasen was able to redeem himself when Buttler tried to take Maharaj on and was caught at deep mid-wicket.
